Package ntnu.idatt2001.ejhaslerjorgfi.util

Class Factory

java.lang.Object
ntnu.idatt2001.ejhaslerjorgfi.util.Factory
public class Factory extends Object

Factory

This class is an implementation of the creational design pattern named Factory Method. The idea behind the class is to provide an interface for creating different objects which share a common denominator such as implementing a certain interface or being sub-classes of a super-class.

The Factory provides methods for creating instances of the Action interface as well as the Goal interface. It is also capable of creating instances of the classes in the model package. By gathering such a facade between the the business model + actions + goals and the graphical user interface, it ensures loose coupling in the software as well as simplifying the process of object creation.

    • createAction

      public static Action createAction(Action.Type type, Object value)
      Creates a new Action object based on the provided goal type and value.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of object to create. The enum alternatives are:
      • GoldAction: Action.Type.GOLD
      • ScoreAction: Action.Type.SCORE
      • HealthAction: Action.Type.HEALTH
      • InventoryAction: Action.Type.INVENTORY
      value - the parameter required for the Action constructor. For InventoryAction, the parameter must be a String, for all others, it must be an integer.
      Returns:
      new Action object.

    • createGoal

      public static Goal createGoal(Goal.Type type, Object value)
      Creates a new Goal object based on the provided goal type and value.
      Parameters:
      type - the type of object to create. The enum alternatives are:
      • GoldGoal: Goal.Type.GOLD
      • ScoreGoal: Goal.Type.SCORE
      • HealthGoal: Goal.Type.HEALTH
      • InventoryGoal: Goal.Type.INVENTORY
      value - the parameter required for the Goal constructor. For InventoryGoal, the parameter must be a list of Strings, for all others, it must be an integer.
      Returns:
      new Goal object.

    • createLink

      public static Link createLink(String text, String reference)
      Creates a new instance of the Link class with its text, representing the nature of the event encountered at the Link as well as a reference to the Passage object it leads to.
      Parameters:
      text - the text which are to be displayed in the Link, must not be null.
      reference - the reference to the leading Passage, must not be null.
      Returns:
      new Link object with the given title and content, or null if either argument is null.

    • createPassage

      public static Passage createPassage(String title, String content)
      Creates a new instance of Passage with its title/identifier as well as the "body" of the event which the Passage represents containing a textual representation of a part of the story.
      Parameters:
      title - the title of the Passage.
      content - the content of the Passage.
      Returns:
      new Passage object with the given title and content, or null if either argument is null.

    • createPlayer

      public static Player createPlayer(String name, int health, int score, int gold)
      Creates a new instance of the Player class with a given name, amount of health points, amount of score points, amount of gold and a collection of items which the Player has in its inventory.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the Player.
      health - health value of the Player represented as health points.
      score - score value of the Player represented as score points.
      gold - amount of gold held by the Player.
      Returns:
      new Player object with the given title and content, or null if either argument is null.

    • createStory

      public static Story createStory(String title, Passage openingPassage)
      Creates a new instance of the Story class with a descriptive title and a Passage acting as the starting point.
      Parameters:
      title - the title of the Story.
      openingPassage - the Passage object which the Story starts from.
      Returns:
      new Story object with the given title and content, or null if either argument is null.

    • createGame

      public static Game createGame(Player player, Story story, List<Goal> goals)
      Creates a new instance of the Game class with a given Player, Story and a collection of Goal objects.
      Parameters:
      player - the Player which will be in the Game.
      story - the Story which the Game will follow.
      goals - collection of Goals which a Player can achieve in the Game.
      Returns:
      new Game object with the given title and content, or null if either argument is null.
